ADS.Text1: Five Night at Freddy’s: Security Breach (FNaF Security Breach for short) is a first-person survival horror game developed by Steel Wool Studios
ADS.Text2: In the game, the player’s goal is to escape a large mall building at night before getting caught by the animatronic animals who are chasing him/he
ADS.Text3: This is the eighth and latest main installment in the long-running Five Night at Freddy’s game series. It’s also the thirteenth game that takes place in the FNaF universe
ADS.Text4: The game was released on 16th December 2021, opening up to mixed reviews.
ADS.Text5: FNaF Security Breach significantly changes the gameplay formula established by the previous entries in the series by being
ADS.Text6: the first FNaF game to have a conventional “free-roam” gameplay, where the player is free to walk around and explore the game’s world
ADS.Text7: the player’s movement and interaction options were restricted to his/her immediate surroundings, and the player wasn’t allowed to walk to other locations
